"caption": "Manjanggul Lava Tube — photo 16"}], "itineraryStops": [{"number": 1, "time": "08:45", "duration": "45 min", "name": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO)", "category": "Alpine Wetland — Ramsar Site + within Hallasan UNESCO World Heritage", "description": "**Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (한라산 1100고지 습지)** is a high-elevation alpine wetland system on the Hallasan plateau, located **at exactly 1,100 m above sea level** along **Route 1100 — the highest national highway in Korea** linking Jeju City to Seogwipo Jungmun. \n\nThe site is a **Ramsar Wetland of International Importance (Site No. 1893, designated 12 October 2009)**, falling within the **Hallasan UNESCO World Heritage Site (2007)**, **Jeju Island UNESCO Biosphere Reserve (2002)**, and **Hallasan National Park (1970)** — making this one of the few sites globally with **four overlapping international/national designations**. \n\nThe wetland comprises **16+ discontinuous freshwater marshes and pools** spread across a low-gradient plateau section that captures and retains rainwater, forming **small permanent lakes and peat bogs** that support diverse floristic assemblages with significant Jeju endemism. Recorded biodiversity includes **3 threatened bird species and 1 threatened plant species within Korea**, plus mammal, reptile, and insect species endemic to Jeju Island. \n\nThe site received **900,000 visitors in 2008** (Mt Halla Visitor Centre data). Visitor experience: a **1-km wooden boardwalk loop** with observation decks, interpretive signage, and a small natural-history exhibit at the trailhead. \n\n**Autumn foliage (October–November)** and **winter snow scenes (December–February)** are the most photographed seasons; **spring + summer** offer wetland flora and endemic species visibility. \n\n**FREE admission**; adjacent **1100 Rest Area (1100 휴게소)** provides indoor restrooms + cafe + small souvenir shop. **Cultural and religious importance** to local communities is documented in the Ramsar listing — historical shaman pilgrimages tied to mountain-water spirits.", "image": "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-21.webp", "highlights": ["**Ramsar Site No. 1893** (designated 12 Oct 2009) — Wetland of International Importance", "**1,100 m above sea level** — on Korea''s **highest national highway** (Route 1100)", "**Quadruple international designation** — Ramsar + UNESCO World Heritage + Biosphere + National Park", "**16+ discontinuous wetlands** — freshwater marshes + pools + peat bogs", "**3 threatened bird + 1 threatened plant** species; multiple Jeju endemics", "**900,000 visitors (2008)** — Mt Halla Visitor Centre managed", "**1-km wooden boardwalk loop** with observation decks + interpretive signage", "**Autumn foliage + winter snow** = signature photographic seasons", "**FREE admission**; adjacent 1100 Rest Area (indoor restroom + cafe)"], "timeUsed": ["Coach arrival + parking at 1100 Rest Area — ~5 min", "Boardwalk loop + observation decks — ~25 min", "Interpretive signage + natural-history exhibit — ~10 min", "Buffer / cafe restroom — ~5 min"], "whyOnRoute": "The 1100 highland is the one Hallasan stop that fits a full-island loop without a reservation or a multi-hour summit hike. A short alpine boardwalk on Korea''s highest highway opens the day inside Hallasan''s UNESCO World Heritage area before the long drive south begins.", "_poi_meta": {"poi_key": "hallasan_1100_wetland", "kb_version": "1.20", "verified_date": "2026-04-29", "sources": ["Ramsar Sites Information Service — 1100 Altitude Wetland (Site No. 1893)", "UNESCO Man and the Biosphere Programme — Jeju Island Biosphere Reserve", "Korea National Park Service — Hallasan National Park 1100 Wetland records", "Mt Halla Visitor Centre — visitor management documentation", "Jeju Special Self-Governing Province — Wetland Protected Area designation 2009"]}, "smartNotes": {"photo": "Boardwalk leading into the wetland with Hallasan in the distance is the iconic shot; autumn (October) gives golden grass colors", "facilities": "Visitor center with snacks and information", "tip": "Bring layers — temperature is 5–10°C cooler than coastal Jeju; check road conditions in winter; combine with Cheonjeyeon Falls if descending south"}, "convenience": {"restroom": "Available at visitor center", "parking": "Free parking at visitor center"}, "visitBasics": {"hours": "Open 24 hours (boardwalk); visitor center 09:00–18:00", "closed": "1100 Highway may close temporarily during heavy snow (Dec–Feb)", "admission": "Free", "walking": "Easy — 1 km wooden boardwalk; flat, accessible"}, "images": ["/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-21.webp", "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-22.webp", "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-23.webp"], "imageCredits": [{"url": "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-21.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-22.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-23.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}], "galleryItems": [{"id": 1, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-21.webp", "location": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO)", "caption": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO) — photo 1", "alt": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO) — gallery image 1"}, {"id": 2, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-22.webp", "location": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO)", "caption": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO) — photo 2", "alt": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO) — gallery image 2"}, {"id": 3, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/hallasan-1100/kakaotalk-20260510-230009595-23.webp", "location": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO)", "caption": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO) — photo 3", "alt": "Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland (Ramsar + UNESCO) — gallery image 3"}]}, {"number": 2, "time": "10:00", "duration": "45 min", "name": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff", "category": "Volcanic Coastline — Hexagonal Columnar-Jointed Lava", "description": "**Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff (대포 주상절리)** is one of Jeju''s clearest examples of columnar basalt along the coast. Lava from Hallasan-area volcanic activity cooled and contracted into tightly packed polygonal stone columns, creating the dramatic cliff line now viewed from a safe seaside deck. \n\nThe columns rise above the waves on the Jungmun coast and are especially photogenic when the sea is active. The visit is short, high-impact, and easier than a long coastal hike, making it a strong stop for mixed-age groups. Walking is mostly on maintained paths and viewing platforms, but wind and sea spray can vary by weather and tide.", "image": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/chatgpt-image-2026-2-15-10-01-04.webp", "highlights": ["**Natural Monument No. 443** — designated **2005-01-06**, the most recent Jeju coastal NM", "Columns rise **30–40 m**, packed in **5- to 7-sided polygons** (mostly hexagons) along **1 km** of coastline", "Formation: **Hallasan flank lava cooled in the sea ~250,000–140,000 years ago**, contracting perpendicular to cooling face", "**East Asia''s premier columnar-jointing site** — peer to Giant''s Causeway, Devils Postpile, Fingal''s Cave", "Wave-spray photos may be possible when the tide and wind conditions are right", "**0.8 km boardwalk loop**, ~15 min walk — barrier-free deck, wheelchair/stroller accessible", "Part of **Jeju Global Geopark (UNESCO 2010-10)** — 13 island-wide geosites", "Admission **₩2,000 adult / ₩1,000 youth / FREE under 7 + over 65**", "Hallasan summit visible to the north on clear days, **directly downstream** geologically"], "timeUsed": ["Parking + ticket purchase + entrance — ~5 min", "Walk to first viewing platform — ~5 min", "Cliff-edge column viewing + photos — ~15 min", "Continue boardwalk loop — ~10 min", "Return to coach — ~10 min"], "whyOnRoute": "Jusangjeolli is the most efficient single demonstration of Jeju''s volcanic geology — a short stop on the south coast that visually summarizes the lava-meets-sea story, on the way between the Hallasan highland and Jeongbang Waterfall.", "_poi_meta": {"poi_key": "daepo_jusangjeolli_cliff", "kb_version": "1.18", "verified_date": "2026-04-29", "sources": ["Cultural Heritage Administration — Natural Monument No. 443 designation (2005-01-06)", "Jeju Global Geopark official site (geopark.jeju.go.kr)", "UNESCO Global Geoparks Network — Jeju (2010 designation)", "VisitJeju — Daepo Jusangjeolli", "Korea Geological Survey — Jeju basalt formation studies"]}, "smartNotes": {"photo": "Wave direction, spray, and side light can change the mood quickly, so wide coastal framing works especially well here.", "facilities": "The entrance area is well equipped, and the viewpoint path itself is relatively straightforward.", "tip": "Even on a sunny day, the coast usually feels colder and windier than inland Jeju."}, "convenience": {"restroom": "Entrance area", "parking": "Parking available (paid lot)"}, "visitBasics": {"hours": "09:00–18:00 (last entry 17:40)", "closed": "Open year-round", "admission": "KRW 2,000 adults / KRW 1,000 children and teens", "walking": "Easy to moderate"}, "images": ["/images/tours/jusangjeolli/chatgpt-image-2026-2-15-10-01-04.webp", "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-11.webp", "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-12.webp", "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-13.webp", "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/photo-005.webp"], "imageCredits": [{"url": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/chatgpt-image-2026-2-15-10-01-04.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-11.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-12.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-13.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/photo-005.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}], "galleryItems": [{"id": 1, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/chatgpt-image-2026-2-15-10-01-04.webp", "location": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff", "caption": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — photo 1", "alt": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — gallery image 1"}, {"id": 2, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-11.webp", "location": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff", "caption": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — photo 2", "alt": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — gallery image 2"}, {"id": 3, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-12.webp", "location": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff", "caption": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — photo 3", "alt": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — gallery image 3"}, {"id": 4, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-13.webp", "location": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff", "caption": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — photo 4", "alt": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — gallery image 4"}, {"id": 5, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/jusangjeolli/photo-005.webp", "location": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff", "caption": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — photo 5", "alt": "Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff — gallery image 5"}]}, {"number": 3, "time": "11:05", "duration": "60 min", "name": "Jeongbang Waterfall", "category": "Coastal Waterfall — Falls Directly Into Ocean (Asia Unique)", "description": "**Jeongbang Falls (정방폭포, ''falls that drop straight to sea'')** is the **only waterfall in Asia that falls directly into the ocean** — a **23 m vertical drop** straight off a basalt cliff into the Pacific, no intermediate pool, no riverbed mouth. \n\nThe cascade is **8 m wide** with a 5 m base pool that reaches the open sea on every tide. This single geographic distinction is why Jeongbang is one of the **''Yeongjusipgyeong (영주십경, 10 Scenic Wonders of Jeju)''** — a Joseon-era literati canon of the island''s most poetic landscapes. \n\nThe Yeongjusipgyeong list, codified by **18th-century Confucian scholar Lee Won-jo (이원조)**, also includes Seongsan Sunrise, Hallasan summit, and Cheonjeyeon — meaning today''s loop covers **3 of the 10** in a single day. Carved on the cliff face beside the falls is the inscription **''Seobulgwacha (서불과차, Seobul Headed Back West)''**, attributed to **Xu Fu (서복)**, the legendary Qin-dynasty alchemist sent by **Emperor Qin Shi Huang (~219 BCE)** to find the elixir of immortality. \n\nLocal lore says he passed through here on his way home — the inscription is the etymological root of the place name **''Seogwipo'' (서귀포, ''where Seo headed back'')**. Access is via **130 stone steps** down to the cove (steepish — knee-friendly footwear recommended). \n\nAdmission: **Adult ₩2,000 / Youth ₩1,000 / FREE under 7 and over 65**. The thunderous spray-cooled microclimate at the base is a noted summer relief spot. \n\n**Local haenyeo (해녀, women divers — UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage 2016)** sometimes sell fresh sea urchin, abalone, and conch directly at the cove on calm-sea days — a rare photographic opportunity to see the diving community at work outside their formal museum context.", "image": "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-15.webp", "highlights": ["**Asia''s only waterfall falling directly into the ocean** — 23 m vertical drop, no riverbed", "Falls are **8 m wide** with a 5 m base pool flushing into the Pacific each tide", "One of the **''Yeongjusipgyeong''** — Joseon-era 10 Scenic Wonders of Jeju", "**''Seobulgwacha'' inscription** — attributed to Xu Fu (Qin alchemist, ~219 BCE), origin of place-name ''Seogwipo''", "**130 stone steps** down to the cove — knee-friendly footwear recommended", "Admission **₩2,000 adult / ₩1,000 youth / FREE under 7 + over 65**", "Spray-cooled microclimate at the base — natural summer relief", "Local **haenyeo (해녀, women divers)** sometimes sell fresh catches at the cove on calm days", "Photographic ''sweet hour'' typically **14:00–14:30** when sun lights the falls face from west"], "timeUsed": ["Entrance + ticket + descent (130 steps) — ~10 min", "Cove viewpoint + falls photography — ~25 min", "Optional cliff-side path + Seobul inscription — ~10 min", "Ascent back to coach — ~10 min", "Buffer — ~5 min"], "whyOnRoute": "Jeongbang — the only waterfall in Asia that falls straight into the sea — sits minutes from Seogwipo''s lunch district, so it slots in just before the midday break without any backtracking.", "_poi_meta": {"poi_key": "jeongbang_falls", "kb_version": "1.18", "verified_date": "2026-04-29", "sources": ["Korea Cultural Heritage Foundation — Yeongjusipgyeong canon", "VisitJeju — Jeongbang Pokpo official listing", "Seogwipo City tourism office — admission and access", "Korea Geological Survey — coastal waterfall inventory", "Jeju Folklore Records — Xu Fu / Seobulgwacha inscription study"]}, "smartNotes": {"photo": "The rocky area below works well for atmosphere-rich shots, but footing and sea spray can make the experience feel more demanding.", "facilities": "Basic facilities are located near the entrance.", "tip": "Because of the stairs and rocky path, it usually feels more physically active on site than it appears on the map."}, "convenience": {"restroom": "Entrance area", "parking": "Parking available"}, "visitBasics": {"hours": "09:00–17:20", "closed": "Open year-round", "admission": "KRW 2,000 adults / KRW 1,000 children", "walking": "Moderate, with stairs"}, "images": ["/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-15.webp", "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-16.webp", "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-17.webp"], "imageCredits": [{"url": "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-15.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-16.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-17.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}], "galleryItems": [{"id": 1, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-15.webp", "location": "Jeongbang Waterfall", "caption": "Jeongbang Waterfall — photo 1", "alt": "Jeongbang Waterfall — gallery image 1"}, {"id": 2, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-16.webp", "location": "Jeongbang Waterfall", "caption": "Jeongbang Waterfall — photo 2", "alt": "Jeongbang Waterfall — gallery image 2"}, {"id": 3, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/jeongbang-falls/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-17.webp", "location": "Jeongbang Waterfall", "caption": "Jeongbang Waterfall — photo 3", "alt": "Jeongbang Waterfall — gallery image 3"}]}, {"number": 4, "time": "12:15", "duration": "60 min", "name": "Lunch — Seogwipo Local", "category": "Midday Reset — Seogwipo Local Cuisine", "description": "**60-minute reset in central Seogwipo (서귀포)** — Jeju''s southern city, famous for fresh seafood landed at **Seogwipo Maeil Olle Market (서귀포매일올레시장)** and the abalone-rich coast. Default rotation depending on season and group size: **galchi-jorim (갈치조림, braised cutlassfish stew)** at a Seogwipo specialist when boats are landing in season (Sep–Feb), **jeonbok-bibimbap (전복비빔밥, abalone over rice)** year-round at a market-facing eatery, or **heuk-doeji gui (흑돼지구이, Jeju black pig BBQ)** for guests preferring grilled meat. \n\nBlack pig (***Sus scrofa* domesticus, Jeju black variety**) was designated **Cultural Heritage Material No. 5 (2015)** and remains a Jeju protected breed. Vegetarian alternative on request: **bibim-guksu (비빔국수, cold spicy noodles)** with seasonal vegetables. \n\nThe lunch spot is **a 5-minute walk from Jeongbang Falls** — guests with appetite for a quick post-lunch coffee can stop at the market''s tea/cafe row before continuing on foot.", "image": null, "highlights": ["Central **Seogwipo** — Jeju''s southern fishing/seafood capital", "**Galchi-jorim (cutlassfish)** in season (Sep–Feb), **jeonbok-bibimbap** year-round", "**Heuk-doeji (Jeju black pig)** option — Cultural Heritage Material No. 5 (2015)", "**Vegetarian bibim-guksu** alternative on request", "Lunch venue **5-min walk from Jeongbang Falls entrance** — minimal coach transit", "Group dietary requirements collected at pickup; menu pre-confirmed"], "timeUsed": ["Walk to lunch venue — ~5 min", "Order + meal + drinks — ~45 min", "Walk to Jeongbang Falls entrance — ~5 min", "Buffer — ~5 min"], "whyOnRoute": "Lunch is placed in central Seogwipo between the south-coast stops and the long eastward drive, so the group resets with energy for the afternoon''s climb and cave.", "smartNotes": {"photo": "Since most of the day centers on landscapes, food photos can help vary the visual rhythm of the route.", "facilities": "Dining-related facilities are usually more than sufficient.", "tip": "It is better to eat at a comfortable pace here than to rush and lose energy for the afternoon."}, "convenience": {"restroom": "Inside the restaurant", "parking": "Parking available"}, "visitBasics": {"hours": "Depends on restaurant operating hours", "closed": "Varies by venue", "admission": "Meal is paid on site unless otherwise specified", "walking": "Minimal"}, "images": []}, {"time": "14:00", "duration": "45 min", "name": "Seongsan Haenyeo Free-Diving Show", "category": "UNESCO Intangible Heritage — Women Divers'' Live Performance", "description": "The haenyeo (women divers) of Jeju are recognized as a UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity (2016). At the cove on the south side of Seongsan Ilchulbong, veteran divers — many in their 60s to 80s — give a daily free-diving demonstration, typically around 13:30 and 15:00. They open with the traditional work songs, then dive 5–10 m with no breathing apparatus to gather conch, sea urchin and abalone, surfacing with the signature ''sumbi-sori'' whistle-breath that lets them release air after a long dive. After the show the divers sell their fresh catch sliced as sashimi right by the water. It is a rare, living encounter with a 400-year matrifocal diving culture that is gradually disappearing as the remaining divers grow older. The demonstration is held in the open air and depends on sea conditions; on days it is cancelled, the route visits the Haenyeo Museum in nearby Hado instead, which tells the same story indoors through dive gear, history and film.", "image": "/images/tours/jeju-haenyeo-museum/haenyeo-sunset-diving-ai.webp", "highlights": ["UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage (2016) — Jeju''s women divers", "Live free-diving demonstration at the Seongsan cove (around 13:30 / 15:00)", "Traditional diving songs and the signature ''sumbi-sori'' breath", "Cancellation alternate: the indoor Haenyeo Museum tells the same story"], "timeUsed": ["Walk down to the haenyeo cove — ~5 min", "Free-diving demonstration + diving songs — ~25 min", "Fresh catch / sashimi by the water — ~10 min", "Return to the vehicle — ~5 min"], "whyOnRoute": "The haenyeo show adds the human, cultural layer to a day of volcanic landforms — and because it sits right at the foot of Seongsan, it costs no extra driving before the climb.", "_poi_meta": {"poi_key": "jeju_haenyeo_museum", "kb_version": "1.29", "verified_date": "2026-06-23", "sources": ["VisitKorea", "UNESCO ICH 2016", "Jeju Haenyeo Museum"]}, "smartNotes": {"photo": "The divers entering the water in their wetsuits, and the fresh catch laid out on the rocks afterward", "facilities": "The divers'' stalls sell fresh sea urchin, conch and abalone sashimi straight from the dive", "tip": "Show timing shifts with the sea and the season — the guide confirms on the day. If it is cancelled you will visit the Haenyeo Museum instead."}, "convenience": {"restroom": "Available at the Seongsan Ilchulbong entrance plaza", "parking": "Shared with the Seongsan Ilchulbong parking lot"}, "visitBasics": {"hours": "Open-air demonstration usually around 13:30 and 15:00 (seasonal and weather dependent)", "closed": "Cancelled in high seas or rough weather; Haenyeo Museum closed Mondays", "admission": "Free to watch the demonstration; Haenyeo Museum (alternate) about ₩1,100 adult", "walking": "Minimal — a short flat path down to the cove"}, "images": ["/images/tours/jeju-haenyeo-museum/haenyeo-sunset-diving-ai.webp"], "imageCredits": [{"url": "/images/tours/jeju-haenyeo-museum/haenyeo-sunset-diving-ai.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}], "galleryItems": [], "number": 5}, {"number": 6, "time": "14:55", "duration": "90 min", "name": "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "category": "UNESCO Tuff Cone — Sunrise Peak (Triple UNESCO Designation)", "description": "**Seongsan Ilchulbong (성산일출봉, ''Sunrise Peak'')** is a **5,000-year-old Surtseyan-type hydrovolcanic tuff cone** — a rare landform created when an underwater basalt eruption broke the sea surface, the magma met seawater, and the resulting steam-explosive ash built a **182 m fortress-shaped crater** rim instead of a typical lava cone. \n\nThe result is what UNESCO formally calls **''an exceptional example of an emergent Surtseyan-type volcanic edifice''**. The crater is **600 m wide × 90 m deep**, ringed by **99 jagged rim rocks** that local lore likens to a stone crown. Seongsan carries the **Triple UNESCO designation**: **World Natural Heritage (inscribed 2007-07-02)** as part of the **''Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes'' property**, **Biosphere Reserve (2002)**, and **Global Geopark (2010-10)** — a stack matched only by Hallasan itself among Korean sites. \n\n**18 Imperial Japanese WWII caves** (kamikaze suicide-boat shelters, 1945) are tunneled into the seaward base. Trail: **0.8 km one-way, ~140 m elevation gain, 60 min round trip** on wide stone steps. \n\n**Haenyeo (해녀) demonstrations** run once daily at 14:00 (1 show/day) at the rocky cove below the cone — Jeju women divers (UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage 2016) descend without scuba gear. \n\nAdmission updated **April 2025**: **Adult ₩5,000 / Youth+Child ₩2,500 / Group adult ₩1,600**, free under 7 and over 65. The summit deck is also part of the **Yeongjusipgyeong (Jeju 10 Scenic Wonders) canon**, and remains Korea''s premier **annual New Year sunrise pilgrimage** destination — 50,000+ visitors ascend before dawn on January 1, with municipal sunrise-festival programming since 1995. \n\n**Udo Island (우도, ''Cow Island'')** — Korea''s largest secondary volcanic island — is clearly visible 4 km offshore from the summit, accessible by **15-min ferry from Seongsan Port** (₩10,500 round-trip) for guests with extra time on a different itinerary.", "image": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-06.webp", "highlights": ["**Triple UNESCO**: World Heritage 2007-07-02 + Biosphere Reserve 2002 + Global Geopark 2010-10", "**5,000 years old** — Surtseyan-type hydrovolcanic eruption, magma-meets-seawater steam-explosive birth", "Crater **600 m wide × 90 m deep**, ringed by **99 jagged rim rocks** (the ''stone crown'')", "**182 m above sea level** — 0.8 km / ~140 m gain, 60-min round trip on stone-step trail", "**18 Imperial Japanese WWII caves** at base — 1945 kamikaze suicide-boat shelters", "**Haenyeo demonstration once daily at 14:00 (subject to bad-weather cancellation)** at the seaside cove — UNESCO Intangible 2016", "**Admission updated April 2025**: Adult ₩5,000 / Youth ₩2,500 / FREE under 7 + over 65", "Spring/autumn hours **05:00–19:00** (last entry 18:20)", "**Closes for first Monday of each month** (occasional rest day)"], "timeUsed": ["Parking + ticket + base brief — ~10 min", "Ascent to summit deck (0.8 km / 140 m gain) — ~30 min", "Summit views + crater rim photos — ~20 min", "Descent — ~20 min", "Optional haenyeo viewing at base (14:00 show; may be canceled in bad weather) — ~10 min"], "whyOnRoute": "Seongsan Ilchulbong is the day''s signature climb — a Triple-UNESCO tuff cone right beside the haenyeo cove, so the group can watch the divers and then climb without any extra driving.", "_poi_meta": {"poi_key": "seongsan_ilchulbong", "kb_version": "1.18", "verified_date": "2026-04-29", "sources": ["UNESCO WHC inscription 1264 (Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes, 2007-07-02)", "UNESCO Global Geoparks Network — Jeju (2010-10 designation)", "Cultural Heritage Administration — Natural Monument designation 2000-07-19", "Seongsan Ilchulbong official site (seongsan.kr) — April 2025 admission update", "Jeju Haenyeo Museum — UNESCO Intangible 2016 inscription record"]}, "smartNotes": {"photo": "Rather than photographing only the summit, wider compositions that include both the crater and coastline usually feel more rewarding.", "facilities": "Facilities at the base area are well developed.", "tip": "Crowds, weather, and group fitness level can all affect how demanding and satisfying the summit experience feels."}, "convenience": {"restroom": "Lower area and surrounding facilities", "parking": "Large parking lot available"}, "visitBasics": {"hours": "Paid entry hours may vary by season", "closed": "Closed on the first Monday of each month (or the following day if it falls on a public holiday)", "admission": "KRW 5,000 adults / KRW 2,500 children", "walking": "Moderate to moderately demanding if you choose to summit"}, "images": ["/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-06.webp", "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-07.webp", "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-08.webp", "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-09.webp", "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-10.webp", "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/photo-006.webp", "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/seongsan-haenyeo-show-ai.webp"], "imageCredits": [{"url": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-06.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-07.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-08.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-09.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-10.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/photo-006.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/seongsan-haenyeo-show-ai.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}, {"url": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/photo-006.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}], "galleryItems": [{"id": 1, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-06.webp", "location": "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "caption": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — photo 1", "alt": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — gallery image 1"}, {"id": 2, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-07.webp", "location": "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "caption": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — photo 2", "alt": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — gallery image 2"}, {"id": 3, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-08.webp", "location": "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "caption": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — photo 3", "alt": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — gallery image 3"}, {"id": 4, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-09.webp", "location": "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "caption": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — photo 4", "alt": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — gallery image 4"}, {"id": 5, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/kakaotalk-20260510-230028438-10.webp", "location": "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "caption": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — photo 5", "alt": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — gallery image 5"}, {"id": 6, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/photo-006.webp", "location": "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "caption": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — photo 6", "alt": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — gallery image 6"}, {"id": 7, "type": "photo", "src": "/images/tours/seongsan-ilchulbong/seongsan-haenyeo-show-ai.webp", "location": "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "caption": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — photo 12", "alt": "Seongsan Ilchulbong — gallery image 12"}], "liveStatusWidget": "haenyeo"}, {"time": "16:55", "duration": "50 min", "name": "Manjanggul Lava Tube", "category": "UNESCO Lava Tube — World Natural Heritage Cave Finale", "description": "Manjanggul is one of the finest lava tubes in the world and the cave at the heart of Jeju''s UNESCO listing. It formed roughly 100,000–300,000 years ago when lava from the Geomunoreum volcanic system drained toward the sea, leaving a tunnel about 7.4 km long. A 1 km section is open to visitors, ending at a 7.6 m lava column — the tallest known lava column on Earth — formed where lava poured down from an upper passage. Along the way the cave shows textbook volcanic features: lava stalactites, lava flowlines striping the walls, rope-like ropy lava on the floor, cave coral, and a ''lava turtle'' rock that, by coincidence, resembles the shape of Jeju Island itself. It is part of the ''Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes'' UNESCO World Heritage Site inscribed in 2007. The cave holds a steady temperature of roughly 11–21 °C year-round, so it is cool in summer and mild in winter — and a natural shelter on a rainy day. The floor is uneven, damp and dimly lit, and the public walk is about 1 km in and back, taking 30–45 minutes. Manjanggul closes periodically for conservation and capacity management; on those days the route visits the nearby Ilchul Land Micheon Cave, another lava tube from the same system.", "image": "/images/tours/ilchulland/chatgpt-image-2026-5-8-07-45-52.webp", "highlights": ["Part of the UNESCO ''Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes'' World Heritage Site (2007)", "Ends at the world''s tallest known lava column — about 7.6 m", "1 km of accessible passage inside a 7.4 km lava-tube system", "Cool 11–21 °C year-round — the day''s natural rain-and-heat shelter"], "timeUsed": ["Arrival + parking at Manjanggul — ~5 min", "Walk in to the 7.6 m lava column — ~20 min", "Lava column + return walk — ~20 min", "Buffer / restroom at entrance — ~5 min"], "whyOnRoute": "Manjanggul caps the loop with the third UNESCO natural-heritage site and the day''s only sheltered, indoor stop. It sits about 30 minutes from Seongsan on the way back toward Jeju City, so it closes the circuit without adding distance.", "_poi_meta": {"poi_key": "manjanggul_lava_tube", "kb_version": "1.29", "verified_date": "2026-06-23", "sources": ["UNESCO World Heritage 2007", "Jeju World Natural Heritage Center", "VisitKorea"]}, "smartNotes": {"photo": "The 7.6 m lava column at the end of the trail and the ''lava turtle'' rock shaped like Jeju Island", "facilities": "Cafe, restrooms and a small shop at the entrance; the Geomunoreum lava-tube system is nearby", "tip": "Bring a light jacket — the cave stays cool year-round — and wear grippy shoes for the wet, uneven floor. On closure days the tour visits the Ilchul Land Micheon Cave lava tube instead."}, "convenience": {"restroom": "Available at the entrance plaza", "parking": "Free parking lot at the entrance"}, "visitBasics": {"hours": "Daily 09:00–18:00 (last entry around 17:10)", "closed": "First Wednesday of each month; periodic conservation closures", "admission": "Adults ₩4,000 / Youth ₩2,000; free for under 7 and over 65", "walking": "Moderate — about 1 km round trip on uneven, damp, dimly lit cave floor with some low ceilings"}, "images": ["/images/tours/ilchulland/chatgpt-image-2026-5-8-07-45-52.webp"], "imageCredits": [{"url": "/images/tours/ilchulland/chatgpt-image-2026-5-8-07-45-52.webp", "source": "atoc-korea"}], "galleryItems": [], "number": 7}], "routeFlowStops": [{"name": "Hallasan 1100", "theme": "Highland", "type": "01"}, {"name": "Jusangjeolli", "theme": "Cliffs", "type": "02"}, {"name": "Jeongbang", "theme": "Waterfall", "type": "03"}, {"name": "Lunch", "theme": "Reset", "type": "04"}, {"name": "Haenyeo Show", "theme": "Culture", "type": "05"}, {"name": "Seongsan", "theme": "Crater", "type": "06"}, {"name": "Manjanggul", "theme": "Lava Tube", "type": "07"}], "routePhases": [{"phase": "Morning — Mountain & South Coast", "duration": "1-3", "description": ""}, {"phase": "Midday — Lunch & Haenyeo Culture", "duration": "4-5", "description": ""}, {"phase": "Finale — Crater & Lava Tube", "duration": "6-7", "description": ""}], "routeShapeIntro": {"title": "How the day flows", "subtitle": "The day runs from the Hallasan 1100 highland through the south-coast cliffs and waterfall, breaks for lunch, then crosses east for a live haenyeo free-diving show, the Seongsan Ilchulbong climb, and the Manjanggul lava tube. About 180 km and roughly 5 hours of driving in total; pickup is usually 08:30–09:00, with return to Jeju City around 18:00–18:30."}, "whyTourWorks": {"bestFor": ["Travelers who only have one day in Jeju", "First-time visitors who want the island''s UNESCO sites", "Travelers who want iconic landmarks and local culture together", "Travelers who enjoy active, full-day sightseeing"], "routeLogicSections": [{"title": "Built to cover Jeju''s best in one day", "icon": "clock-3", "iconBg": "bg-amber-50/80", "items": [{"label": "Open on the Hallasan highland", "detail": "Starting at the 1,100 m alpine wetland sets the day against Jeju''s mountain core before the long cross-island drive begins."}, {"label": "Keep the south coast in the middle", "detail": "Jusangjeolli, Jeongbang and lunch hold the west-to-east flow together while keeping the visual density high through midday."}, {"label": "Finish in the east with crater and cave", "detail": "Haenyeo culture, the Seongsan climb and the Manjanggul lava tube turn the eastern leg into a strong UNESCO finale rather than a string of separate stops."}]}, {"title": "Why this day feels especially substantial", "icon": "mountain", "iconBg": "bg-sky-50/80", "items": [{"label": "Three UNESCO World Heritage sites", "detail": "Hallasan, Seongsan Ilchulbong and Manjanggul are all part of Jeju''s UNESCO inscription — the highest UNESCO density possible in a single Jeju day."}, {"label": "A living cultural layer", "detail": "The haenyeo free-diving show adds UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage to a day otherwise built on volcanic landforms."}, {"label": "Maximum value for the time", "detail": "Mountain, cliffs, waterfall, culture, crater and cave in one circuit — designed so a single day still feels like a complete Jeju trip."}]}, {"title": "When on-site conditions change", "icon": "wind", "iconBg": "bg-slate-50/80", "items": [{"label": "Haenyeo show is weather-dependent", "detail": "The open-air free-diving demonstration can be cancelled in high seas; on those days the route visits the Haenyeo Museum instead."}, {"label": "Manjanggul has periodic closures", "detail": "If the lava tube is closed for conservation or capacity, the nearby Ilchul Land Micheon Cave lava tube is used as the alternate."}, {"label": "Return time may shift slightly", "detail": "Traffic, group walking speed and crowd levels can all cause small changes to the final return time."}]}], "lessIdealFor": ["Travelers who prefer a slow, relaxed pace", "Travelers who want to avoid stairs or uphill walking", "Groups traveling with very young children", "Guests who are uncomfortable in cool, dim cave passages"]}, "practicalAccordionItems": [{"id": "pickup", "title": "Pickup and Return Times", "preview": "Early start, return to Jeju City in the evening", "content": ["Pickup in Jeju City between 08:30 and 09:00", "Return to Jeju City around 18:00–18:30", "Airport pickup can be arranged depending on circumstances", "Final meeting time is confirmed the night before"]}, {"id": "walking", "title": "Walking and Terrain", "preview": "Active route with stairs, a climb and a cave", "content": ["Hallasan 1100 Wetland is an easy 1 km boardwalk loop.", "Jeongbang Waterfall includes stairs and a rocky walking path.", "Seongsan Ilchulbong is a stair climb if the group chooses to summit.", "Manjanggul is about 1 km round trip on uneven, damp, dimly lit cave floor.", "Comfortable shoes with good grip are strongly recommended."]}, {"id": "weather", "title": "Weather and Closure Adjustments", "preview": "Usually runs as planned, with built-in alternates", "content": ["Light rain: the tour usually runs as normal — the cave is a natural shelter", "High seas: the haenyeo free-diving show may be replaced by the Haenyeo Museum", "Manjanggul closure: the nearby Ilchul Land Micheon Cave lava tube is used instead", "Winter: the Hallasan 1100 highland can be snowy or icy — the route may adjust stay times"]}, {"id": "flight", "title": "If You Arrive in or Leave Jeju the Same Day", "preview": "You need a generous evening buffer", "content": ["This is a high-density route covering Jeju''s signature highlights in one day.", "Same-day arrival or departure can work, but only if you leave enough evening buffer.", "A late flight is strongly recommended.", "Please factor in traffic, walking pace and on-site conditions when judging timing risk."]}, {"id": "wear", "title": "What to Wear and Bring", "preview": "Walking shoes, layers and a light jacket for the cave", "content": ["Walking shoes with good grip", "Layered clothing for mountain, coast and cave temperature differences", "A light jacket — Manjanggul stays cool year-round", "Hat and sun protection", "Water bottle"]}, {"id": "included", "title": "What''s Included / Not Included", "preview": "Guide, vehicle, pickup and all admissions included", "variant": "included", "content": ["Professional English-speaking guide", "Small-group vehicle", "Jeju City hotel pickup and drop-off", "All admission tickets (Hallasan 1100, Jusangjeolli, Jeongbang, Seongsan, Manjanggul / Haenyeo Museum on alternate days)", "Bottled water", "Lunch (pay on site)", "Personal shopping expenses", "Guide gratuities"]}], "practicalWeatherStatic": {"today": {"temp": "—", "label": "Live weather integration"}, "tomorrow": {"temp": "—", "label": "Updated daily"}, "_seasonalSummary": "A full-island loop covering east, south, and west Jeju in one day. Weather can vary between regions — coastal stops mild year-round, but inland transit can be cooler and windier.", "_seasonalTemperatures": [{"season": "Spring (Mar–May)", "range": "8–22°C", "notes": "Cherry blossoms on east coast in early April; mild driving conditions."}, {"season": "Summer (Jun–Aug)", "range": "22–30°C", "notes": "Hot but humidity moderated by coastal driving. Cheonjiyeon falls at peak flow."}, {"season": "Autumn (Sep–Nov)", "range": "10–24°C", "notes": "Best season — clearest visibility across all stops, comfortable walking temps."}, {"season": "Winter (Dec–Feb)", "range": "3–10°C", "notes": "Wind chill significant at Seongsan rim and Jusangjeolli cliffs. Fewer crowds at all stops."}]}, "seasonalVariations": [{"season": "Spring", "description": "Mountain air feels especially fresh, and island-wide visibility is often cleaner and brighter."}, {"season": "Summer", "description": "Days are longest, and the coastal colors tend to feel the most vivid and saturated."}, {"season": "Autumn", "description": "Clear skies often make the full-island route feel especially satisfying from start to finish."}, {"season": "Winter", "description": "The air turns sharper and clearer, and the contrast between mountain and sea becomes even stronger."}], "bookingTrustItems": [{"icon": "clock-3", "title": "Jeju''s best, in a single day", "description": "Three UNESCO sites plus haenyeo culture", "iconBg": "bg-emerald-50/80", "body": "Licensed local operator designing this loop for travelers who have one day and want Jeju''s most recognizable landmarks — a Hallasan highland, columnar cliffs, an ocean waterfall, a living haenyeo show, the Seongsan tuff cone and the Manjanggul lava tube — in a single circuit."}, {"icon": "mountain", "title": "Focused on iconic landmarks", "description": "From the Hallasan highland to a UNESCO lava tube", "iconBg": "bg-sky-50/80", "body": "Route specialists who run the full-island loop regularly — the stop sequence minimizes backtracking and times the south-coast and haenyeo stops to tide, light and demonstration schedules."}, {"icon": "users", "title": "Small-group operation", "description": "Better able to adapt to closures and on-site conditions", "iconBg": "bg-amber-50/80", "body": "Small-group format keeps the day flexible — the guide can swap the haenyeo show for the museum, or Manjanggul for the Ilchul Land lava tube, without breaking the route."}], "bookingSupportSteps": [{"timing": "After booking", "title": "Instant confirmation", "detail": "A booking confirmation is sent with a summary of the route.", "description": "Instant confirmation with Jeju City hotel pickup details."}, {"timing": "12 hours before", "title": "Pre-departure reminder", "detail": "Weather notes and route adjustment guidance are shared in advance.", "description": "Pre-tour note on Seongsan rim conditions and Jeongbang Waterfall access."}, {"timing": "The night before", "title": "Final pickup notice", "detail": "You receive your exact pickup time and contact details.", "description": "Final pickup time confirmed the evening before."}, {"timing": "Morning of departure", "title": "Day-of route note", "detail": "Any latest on-site updates are briefly shared before departure.", "description": "Morning message with weather summary and any adjustment."}, {"timing": "During the tour", "title": "Stop-by-stop guidance", "detail": "Key information is shared at each stop as needed.", "description": "Guide narrates Hallasan''s shield-volcano geology, columnar joint formation at Jusangjeolli, and Seongsan''s Surtseyan-eruption birth story."}, {"timing": "After the tour", "title": "Post-tour support", "detail": "Follow-up support and additional recommendations are available if needed.", "description": "Post-tour feedback request sent after return."}], "staticQuestions": [{"id": "one-day", "question": "If I only have one day in Jeju, is this the right route?", "answer": "Yes. This route is built to cover Jeju''s core landmarks — three UNESCO sites, haenyeo culture, cliffs and a waterfall — in one day, at a faster pace than a standard day tour."}, {"id": "unesco", "question": "Which stops are the UNESCO sites?", "answer": "Three: the Hallasan 1100 highland (part of the Hallasan World Heritage area), Seongsan Ilchulbong, and the Manjanggul lava tube — all within Jeju''s ''Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes'' inscription. The haenyeo show is also UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage."}, {"id": "haenyeo", "question": "What happens if the haenyeo show is cancelled?", "answer": "The open-air free-diving demonstration depends on sea conditions. If it is cancelled, the route visits the Haenyeo Museum nearby, which tells the same women-divers'' story indoors."}, {"id": "manjanggul", "question": "Is Manjanggul always open?", "answer": "Manjanggul closes periodically for conservation and capacity. When it is closed, the tour visits the nearby Ilchul Land Micheon Cave — another lava tube from the same volcanic system — instead."}, {"id": "tiring", "question": "Will this route feel tiring?", "answer": "It is more active than a typical small-group day tour: the route covers most of the island and includes the Seongsan climb, the Jeongbang stairs and the Manjanggul cave walk."}, {"id": "flight", "question": "Can I join if I arrive in or leave Jeju on the same day?", "answer": "Possibly, but only with a generous evening buffer. If your flight timing is tight, this route is not recommended."}, {"id": "manjanggul-last", "question": "Why is Manjanggul scheduled last?", "answer": "It sits on the way back toward Jeju City and works as a cool, sheltered UNESCO finale after a long day of open-air landforms."}], "guestReviews": [], "reviewsSummary": {"avera