: "first_time_jeju_intro_loop", "competing_tours_count": 3, "china_mainland_market_fit": 0, "korea_domestic_market_fit": 0, "taiwan_market_fit": 1, "singapore_market_fit": 1, "hong_kong_market_fit": 1, "china_diaspora_overseas_market_fit": 0.95, "se_asia_market_fit": 0.95, "us_market_fit": 0.85, "europe_market_fit": 0.85, "australia_market_fit": 0.85, "japan_market_fit": 0.85}, "matching_metadata": {"primary_themes": ["jeju", "highlights", "unesco", "first_time_jeju", "island_wide"], "secondary_themes": ["volcano_geology", "columnar_jointing", "tuff_cone", "ocean_waterfall", "lava_tube", "haenyeo_culture", "world_natural_heritage", "intangible_heritage"], "best_for": ["first_time_jeju", "couples", "small_families", "history_lovers", "geology_enthusiasts", "photographers", "honeymoon_travelers"], "not_recommended_for": ["thrill_seekers", "private_tour_seekers", "off_season_volcanic_visitors", "wheelchair_users", "very_young_kids_under_5", "guests_avoiding_stairs"], "anchor_pois": ["Hallasan 1100 Altitude Wetland", "Daepo Jusangjeolli", "Jeongbang Falls", "Seongsan Haenyeo Show", "Seongsan Ilchulbong", "Manjanggul Lava Tube"], "anchor_poi_keys": ["hallasan_1100_wetland", "daepo_jusangjeolli_cliff", "jeongbang_falls", "jeju_haenyeo_museum", "seongsan_ilchulbong", "manjanggul_lava_tube"], "reviews_attribution": null, "unesco_fit_note": "unesco_fit=5: three UNESCO World Heritage natural sites on one route from the Jeju Volcanic Island and Lava Tubes inscription (2007) — Hallasan, Seongsan Ilchulbong and the Manjanggul lava tube — plus the haenyeo free-diving show (UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage, 2016). Highest possible UNESCO density for a one-day Jeju tour.", "competing_products": ["southwest-hallasan-osulloc-aewol", "east-signature-nature-core", "jeju-southern-top-unesco-spots-tour", "jeju-eastern-unesco-spots-day-tour"], "audit_summary": "Grand highlights loop covering three UNESCO World Heritage sites in one day — Hallasan (1100 alpine wetland), Seongsan Ilchulbong (Surtseyan tuff cone) and the Manjanggul lava tube — plus a living haenyeo free-diving show (UNESCO Intangible Heritage), the Jusangjeolli columnar cliffs and the ocean-falling Jeongbang Waterfall. About 180 km and ~5 hours driving across a ~10.5-hour day. The single most representative high-intensity intro to Jeju for first-time visitors.", "score_rationale": {"high_scores": {"first_time_jeju_fit=1.0": "Single best intro to Jeju''s UNESCO + volcanic identity; covers 3 cardinal directions (N/S/E) in one day", "unesco_taste_fit=1.0": "Hallasan UNESCO + Seongsan Triple UNESCO in same day = unmatched in catalog", "geology_enthusiast_fit=1.0": "Three distinct volcanic landforms (parasitic cone, columnar lava, tuff cone) sequenced as eruptive history", "instagrammable_fit=1.0": "Four of the most photographed Jeju locations on a single loop", "asia_unique_landform_fit=1.0": "Jeongbang = only ocean-falling waterfall in Asia"}, "low_scores": {"private_tour_fit=0.05": "Format is small-group fixed itinerary only", "wheelchair_accessible_anchor_fit=0.4": "Hallasan trail + Jeongbang 130 steps + Seongsan ascent block wheelchair access", "off_season_fit=0.6": "Winter Hallasan accessibility caveat + cone summit cold", "rain_fit=0.5": "All 4 substantive stops are outdoor; no indoor fallback anchor", "west_jeju_fit=0.3": "Loop deliberately excludes west (covered by sister tour southwest-hallasan-osulloc-aewol)"}}, "differentiation_vs_southwest_sister": "Same Hallasan + Jusangjeolli openers, but **east-coastal anchor at Seongsan Triple UNESCO** (sister terminates at Aewol Cafe Street west-coast). This tour = UNESCO + geology emphasis; sister = tea culture + sunset cafe lifestyle. Pair complementarily for guests with 2 days on Jeju: this loop on Day 1 (UNESCO landmarks), sister on Day 2 (southwest cultural depth).", "seasonal_window": {"best_months": ["April", "May", "October", "November"], "good_months": ["March", "June", "September"], "caveat_months": ["July", "August (monsoon)", "December", "January (Hallasan ice)"], "peak_crowd_months": ["April (cherry)", "October (foliage)"]}, "kb_anchor_version": "1.29"}, "itinerary_variants": [], "_publication": {"schema_version": "v4_canonical", "last_modified": "2026-06-23", "version_history": ["v1_smallgroup", "v15_unified"], "fix_passes": {"v15_unified": "Migrated from small-group v1 schema to v15 canonical: schema_version 1→7; SEO expanded (primaryKeywords, ogImage, title); price expanded (priceSource, priceNote, discountPercent); routeFlowStops id→type; routePhases stripped of Tailwind classes (bgClass/dotClass/textClass), reshaped to {phase,duration,description}; seasonalVariations stripped of Tailwind, reshaped to {season,description}; whyTourWorks.lessIdeal→lessIdealFor; practicalWeatherStatic gained _seasonalSummary and _seasonalTemperatures; matching_profile expanded to v15 canonical (≥40 fields with anchor_poi_keys, vehicle_type_legacy, seasonality, fit-vector full set); matching_metadata reformatted to anchor_pois/anchor_poi_keys/primary_themes/secondary_themes/best_for/not_recommended_for/reviews_attribution/unesco_fit_note shape; pickup_dropoff added (Schema A.1); itinerary_variants=[]; _publication block added. PRESERVED from source (richer than catalog v15): itineraryStops[*].visitBasics, .convenience, .smartNotes (operational data), guestReviews[4 each], reviewsSummary.highlights.", "v17_batch1_enhancement": {"date": "2026-04-28", "description": "Batch 1 deep enhancement — descriptions raised to 700-1100+ chars from ~210 chars; KB-backed visitBasics/convenience/smartNotes/_poi_meta on all attraction stops; matching_profile adjusted with verified-fact reasoning (see _score_audit).", "_score_audit": {"_methodology": "Scores use the current 0-1 float scale.", "scale_note": "Current live matching uses 0-1 float scores in match_tours.matching_profile.", "deltas_applied": {"unesco_fit": {"old": 5, "new": 5, "reasoning": "Confirmed: 2 of 4 attraction stops are UNESCO-designated (Hallasan WHS+Biosphere 2002/2007, Seongsan WHS 2007 + Global Geopark 2010 + part of Jeju Volcanic Island & Lava Tubes property). Score remains 5/5 — verified."}, "walking_level": {"old": 4, "new": 4, "reasoning": "Verified totals: Eoseungsaengak 1.3 km + 200 m gain (60 min RT), Jusangjeolli 0.8 km flat (15 min), Jeongbang 130 stairs + rocky terrain (~30 min), Seongsan 0.8 km + 140 m gain via 300-500 steps (45-60 min). Total ~4 km walking + ~340 m elevation across 3 stair-heavy stops. 4/5 confirmed."}, "iconic_landmark_fit": {"old": 5, "new": 5, "reasoning": "All 4 attractions are verified Jeju iconic landmarks: Hallasan (Korea''s tallest peak), Jusangjeolli (Korea''s largest columnar lava, NM443), Jeongbang (only Asia waterfall into ocean), Seongsan (Triple-UNESCO crown). 5/5 verified."}, "value_for_money_fit": {"old": 5, "new": 5, "reasoning": "Verified entrance fees: Hallasan free, Jusangjeolli ₩2,000, Jeongbang ₩2,000, Seongsan ₩2,000 = ₩6,000 total per adult attraction fees. Lowest combined-fee headline route on Jeju. 5/5 confirmed."}, "weather_sensitivity": {"old": 4, "new": 5, "reasoning": "UPGRADED 4→5. Three of the four attractions are exposed: Hallasan trail icy in winter (microspikes per AllTrails), Jusangjeolli wave spray reaches 20 m at high tide, Jeongbang rocks slippery when wet, Seongsan summit windy and exposed. Only the lunch is indoor. Verified high weather dependence."}, "young_kids_fit": {"old": 3, "new": 2, "reasoning": "DOWNGRADED 3→2. Verified: Eoseungsaengak 200 m elevation gain via wooden stairs (challenging for under-7s); Jeongbang 130 stairs + rocky terrain (not stroller-friendly, slippery); Seongsan 300-500 steps (Wikipedia: ''not stroller-friendly''). Three stair-heavy stops in one day exceeds typical young-kids tolerance."}, "stroller_fit": {"old": 2, "new": 1, "reasoning": "DOWNGRADED 2→1. Three of four attractions explicitly not stroller-accessible per official sources: Eoseungsaengak (wooden stairs through forest), Jeongbang (130 stone stairs + rocky terrain), Seongsan (300-500 wooden deck steps). Only Jusangjeolli is stroller-friendly. 1/5 verified."}, "mobility_friendly_fit": {"old": 3, "new": 2, "reasoning": "DOWNGRADED 3→2. Three out of four stops have significant stair/elevation requirements per verified trail data. Mobility-restricted guests would only comfortably do Jusangjeolli."}, "rain_fit": {"old": 3, "new": 2, "reasoning": "DOWNGRADED 3→2. Verified: Eoseungsaengak wooden stairs slippery when wet (AllTrails reviews), Jeongbang rocky terrain to base ''very slippery when wet'' (Brit Adventures, expatolife), Seongsan stairs become slippery. Only Jusangjeolli viewing decks have railings. Heavy rain would compromise 3 of 4 stops."}, "solo_traveler_fit": {"old": 5, "new": 5, "reasoning": "Small group format + iconic-only stops + clear schedule = strong solo fit. Confirmed."}, "scenic_level": {"old": 5, "new": 5, "reasoning": "All 4 stops are top-tier scenic per multiple verified sources (UNESCO designations, CNN/designboom recognition equivalents). 5/5 confirmed."}, "photo_level": {"old": 5, "new": 5, "reasoning": "Each stop has documented iconic photo spots (Eoseungsaengak Tochika+vista, Jusangjeolli high-tide spray, Jeongbang waterfall-meets-sea, Seongsan crater rim). 5/5 confirmed."}, "hiking_fit": {"old": "MISSING", "new": 4, "reasoning": "ADDED. With 2 verified hiking trails (Eoseungsaengak 1.3 km +200 m, Seongsan 0.8 km +140 m) totaling ~4 km of stair-climbing, this is a meaningfully hike-forward route. NOTE: this field doesn''t exist in 1-5 scale schema; flagged for Jason''s review whether to add."}, "natural_landscape_fit": {"old": "MISSING", "new": 5, "reasoning": "ADDED-PROPOSAL. Volcanic geology (Hallasan + Jusangjeolli + Seongsan) + waterfall = 100% natural attractions. NOTE: not in 1-5 schema currently."}}}, "stops_enhanced": 5, "sources": ["VisitKorea", "Wikipedia", "Hallasan National Park", "AllTrails", "Trazy", "Inside Jeju", "World of Waterfalls", "Trip.com Korea"]}, "v17_schema_unification": {"date": "2026-04-28", "description": "Phase 1: Standardized matching_profile scores to the current 0-1 float scale used by match_tours.matching_profile.", "fields_converted": 43, "fields_skipped": 0, "fields_already_float": 0}, "v18_course_change_2026_06_23": "Course changed to 7-stop UNESCO grand loop: Hallasan 1100 highland → Jusangjeolli → Jeongbang → lunch → Seongsan haenyeo free-diving show (museum alternate) → Seongsan Ilchulbong climb → Manjanggul lava tube (Ilchul Land Micheon Cave alternate). Price → US$100 (≈ ₩138,000). Duration → 10–10.5h, ~180 km, ~5h driving. stopsCount 5→7. Eoseungsaengak swapped for the 1100 wetland; Haenyeo and Manjanggul added. Matching raised: culture 2→3, local_culture_fit 3→4, intangible_heritage_fit 2→4, storytelling 4→5, indoor_ratio 28→32, rain_fit 2→3, duration_band→10.5h. Pickup/drop-off unchanged."}}}'::jsonb
)
